{
  "page": "Old inn on Eel Alley",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>old inn on Eel Alley</b><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> is an inn in <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Its location is well away from watchful eyes.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Layout\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Layout</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Game_of_Thrones\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Layout\">Layout</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Old_inn_on_Eel_Alley&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Layout\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Found halfway up <a href=\"/index.php/Visenya%27s_Hill\" title=\"Visenya&#39;s Hill\">Visenya's Hill</a>, the establishment is a rambling old place on <a href=\"/index.php/Eel_Alley\" title=\"Eel Alley\">Eel Alley</a>. Some of its rooms have a view of the <a href=\"/index.php/Blackwater_Rush\" title=\"Blackwater Rush\">Blackwater Rush</a> and the rooftops of <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Varys\" title=\"Varys\">Varys</a> considers it a dismal hovel.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The old woman who owns the inn has a wandering eye.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Old_inn_on_Eel_Alley&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>After Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a> earned his <a href=\"/index.php/Knighthood\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Knighthood\">knighthood</a> against the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingswood_Brotherhood\" title=\"Kingswood Brotherhood\">Kingswood Brotherhood</a>, he stopped at <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> before returning to <a href=\"/index.php/Casterly_Rock\" title=\"Casterly Rock\">Casterly Rock</a>. His twin sister, <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a>, visited Jaime at the inn off <a href=\"/index.php/Eel_Alley\" title=\"Eel Alley\">Eel Alley</a>, with Cersei dressing as a simple serving wench so she could evade the guards of their father, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">Tywin Lannister</a>. The incestuous twins spent the night together, with Cersei convincing Jaime to join the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a> and thereby remain close to her in the capital and avoid marrying <a href=\"/index.php/Lysa_Arryn\" title=\"Lysa Arryn\">Lysa Tully</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Old_inn_on_Eel_Alley&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Game_of_Thrones\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Old_inn_on_Eel_Alley&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Game of Thrones\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>After they disembark the <i><a href=\"/index.php/Storm_Dancer\" title=\"Storm Dancer\">Storm Dancer</a></i>, Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Stark\" title=\"Catelyn Stark\">Catelyn Stark</a> and Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Rodrik_Cassel\" title=\"Rodrik Cassel\">Rodrik Cassel</a> move into the modest old inn halfway up <a href=\"/index.php/Visenya%27s_Hill\" title=\"Visenya&#39;s Hill\">Visenya's Hill</a>. The inn was suggested by the ship's captain <a href=\"/index.php/Moreo_Tumitis\" title=\"Moreo Tumitis\">Moreo Tumitis</a>. Catelyn pays a copper to the two crewmembers who help with the traveler's chests.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>After Rodrik leaves to find Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Aron_Santagar\" title=\"Aron Santagar\">Aron Santagar</a> at the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Keep\" title=\"Red Keep\">Red Keep</a>, Catelyn stays away from the common room and tries to get some sleep. She is woken by the <a href=\"/index.php/City_Watch_of_King%27s_Landing\" title=\"City Watch of King&#39;s Landing\">City Watch of King's Landing</a>, who show her a seal depicting a <a href=\"/index.php/Mockingbird\" title=\"Mockingbird\">mockingbird</a> in grey wax—the sigil of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Petyr_Baelish\" title=\"Petyr Baelish\">Petyr Baelish</a>. As she prepares to accompany the soldiers to the Red Keep, Catelyn wonders how Petyr knew she was in King's Landing and settles on Moreo as the culprit. When Catelyn asks Petyr how he knew she was in the city, he tells her that Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Varys\" title=\"Varys\">Varys</a> knows all. Varys explains that Rodrik has returned to the inn with Aron, and that the two are drinking in the common room while waiting for Catelyn to return.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Old_inn_on_Eel_Alley&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Some time in the middle of the night, as Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a> is standing vigil over his father <a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">Tywin's</a> funeral bier in the <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Sept_of_Baelor\" title=\"Great Sept of Baelor\">Great Sept of Baelor</a>, Queen Regent <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a> visits her twin with news of the refusal of their uncle, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Kevan_Lannister\" title=\"Kevan Lannister\">Kevan Lannister</a>, to become <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a>. Cersei is in disguise, dressed as a tavern wench. She asks Jaime if he remembers the first time she came to him like this, in some dismal inn off Weasel Alley. Jaime corrects her, saying it was Eel Alley.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Old_inn_on_Eel_Alley&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The woman who owned it was a sour crone with a wandering eye who looked them over suspiciously and bit the coin that Catelyn offered her to make sure it was real. Her rooms were large and airy, though, and <a href=\"/index.php/Moreo_Tumitis\" title=\"Moreo Tumitis\">Moreo</a> swore that her fish stew was the most savory in all the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a>. Best of all, she had no interest in their names.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Stark\" title=\"Catelyn Stark\">Catelyn Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>I think it best if you stay away from the common room. Even in a place like this, one never knows who may be watching.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Rodrik_Cassel\" title=\"Rodrik Cassel\">Rodrik Cassel</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Stark\" title=\"Catelyn Stark\">Catelyn Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>I assure you, Lady Stark, nothing at all has been done to the good <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knight</a>. He did call here early this afternoon. He visited with Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Aron_Santagar\" title=\"Aron Santagar\">Aron Santagar</a> in the armory, and they talked of <a href=\"/index.php/Littlefinger%27s_blade\" title=\"Littlefinger&#39;s blade\">a certain dagger</a>. About sunset, they left <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Keep\" title=\"Red Keep\">the castle</a> together and walked to that dreadful hovel where you were staying. They are still there, drinking in the common room, waiting for your return. Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Rodrik_Cassel\" title=\"Rodrik Cassel\">Rodrik</a> was very distressed to find you gone.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Varys\" title=\"Varys\">Varys</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Stark\" title=\"Catelyn Stark\">Catelyn Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Old_inn_on_Eel_Alley&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords-Chapter_11\" title=\"A Storm of Swords-Chapter 11\">Chapter 11</a>, Jaime II.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\">2.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\">2.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\">2.4</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-5\">2.5</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-6\">2.6</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-7\">2.7</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-8\">2.8</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones-Chapter_18\" title=\"A Game of Thrones-Chapter 18\">Chapter 18</a>, Catelyn IV.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">3.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\">3.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_8\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Chapter 8\">Chapter 8</a>, Jaime I.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260404202604\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.030 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.03